      "name": "📚 Quick Start Guide",
      "description": "Start here! Follow these steps to test everything:",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1️⃣ Step 1 - Seed Database",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/docs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "docs"]
            },
            "description": "⚠️ IMPORTANT: Before running any tests:\n\n**In your terminal, run:**\n```\nnode seed.js\n```\n\nThis will create sample users and data in your database.\n\nThen come back to Postman and click 'Send' on the next steps."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2️⃣ Step 2 - Login All Users",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/docs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "docs"]
            },
            "description": "Run these login requests in order to get tokens for all roles:\n\n1. Go to 'Authentication' folder\n2. Click 'Login as Admin 1'\n3. Click 'Login as Doctor 1'\n4. Click 'Login as Patient 1'\n\nThe tokens will be automatically saved to variables (adminToken, doctorToken, patientToken)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3️⃣ Step 3 - Run Test Collections",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/docs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "docs"]
            },
            "description": "Now you can test all features:\n\n✅ **Use the Runner feature:**\n1. Click 'Runner' button in Postman\n2. Select this collection\n3. Click 'Run'\n4. Watch all tests execute automatically\n\n✅ **Or test manually:**\n- Follow the folder structure (Specializations → Services → Appointments → Payments → Reviews → Dashboards)\n- Copy-paste IDs from responses into variables when needed\n- Check 'Pre-request Script' and 'Tests' tabs for automatic variable extraction"
          }
        }
